<paragraph blockId="155.[189,310,1209,1235]" box="[189,310,1209,1235]" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1209,1235]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1209,1235]" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="155.[189,1399,1257,1430]" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hess" authorityYear="1964" box="[320,465,1258,1283]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Dermocoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="155" pageNumber="156" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[320,465,1258,1283]" italics="true" pageId="155" pageNumber="156">Dermocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with large LAPs displaying a very well-developed vertical striation on at least half of the outer surface; large, oval and conspicuously oblique spur on proximal edge; four spine articulations sunken in deep notches of a poorly elevated distal LAP portion; ridge on inner side very slender, with ventral tip merged with ventral portion of LAP, and dorsal tip slightly widened and merged with proximal edge of LAP.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
